(cont.) however he wants
column4: trying bury his problems in it. But as the saying goes "money can't buy happiness." @IGN @_MxttKsog -DD

text: .@IGN @_MxttKsog Harry loves to drive fast cars
column5: and go to clubs. He has lots of money and spends it...

text: RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @_MxttKsog What do you think Harry would do for fun? #AskDaneDeHaan
(cont.) He is heir to the most powerful cooperation in the world... And he's not afraid to use it. @IGN @Leonaradoiscool -DD
.@IGN @Leonaradoiscool Harry uses the money and power that had been inherently bestowed on him to his advantage...
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @Leonaradoiscool: How do you give your character his edge? #AskDaneDeHaan
(cont.) being disappointed by him and trying to kill him I've come to admire the villains more. #OsbornArmy @IGN @GwenStacyParker -DD
.@IGN @GwenStacyParker Going into it my favorite character was probably Spider Man himself... But since I spent all day for 6 months...
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @GwenStacyParker: Who is your favorite character from Spider-Man? #AskDaneDeHaan
(cont.) becomes the Green Goblin. The scene of the actual transformation is one of my favorites in the movie. @IGN @Surewhy_not -DD
(cont.) But the script is awesome and everything is rooted in truth. It is the origin story of how Harry Osborn... @IGN @Surewhy_not
.@IGN @Surewhy_not Thanks! The journey I go through in this movie is probably the most extreme arc of a character I've ever done...
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @Surewhy_not: Big fan Dane. How was the transformation from a sort of calm Harry to a crazy green goblin? #AskDan‚Ä¶
(cont.) It's a true work of art. Prototype Oscorp Body Armor. @IGN @SereneCN -DD
.@IGN @SereneCN The suit weighs 50lbs. It was designed by @wetaworkshop and our costume designer Deb Scott...
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @SereneCN: Wearing Green Goblin costume on set must be a unique experience
column4: tell us some stories about it. #AskDa‚Ä¶

text: .@IGN @thegamercatfish The fight scenes!  To spend an entire day trying to kill Spider-Man is nothing short of amazing. #PunIntended -DD
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @thegamercatfish: What did you enjoy most when you were filming your scenes as the Green Goblin? #AskDaneDehaan
(cont.) bringing him into modern day. We have never had a Harry Osborn of today! - DD @IGN @TrueWebSlinger
(cont.) for me to be faithful to who Harry has always been while still... @IGN @TrueWebSlinger
(cont.) to make sure I was honoring the Harry that has been around for almost 50 years. It was always important... @IGN @TrueWebSlinger
.@IGN @TrueWebSlinger I grew up going to the original movies as a kid so I knew a bit
column4: but I did a lot of research...

text: RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @TrueWebSlinger: How much did you know about the character Harry Osborn and how much research did you have to do?
(cont.) he looked like "Elvis and Bert had a baby" @IGN @spockla -DD
.@IGN @spockla A bit of improving especially with Andrew. Sad to say @MarcW cut the part where I told Andrew...
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @spockla: Did you improv anything for your character? Lines
.@IGN @knottgregson I probably did about 75% of the ones we actually filmed but a lot of them are CGI. -DD
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @knottgregson What percentage of the stunts in this film would you say you actually did yourself? #AskDaneDehaan
(cont.) Same diet and trainer as Andrew. By the end of the shoot I was eating 5500 calories a day. @IGN @1VictoriaAngela -DD
.@IGN @1VictoriaAngela Yes I worked out like a mad man 6 days a week and was on a very specific diet...
RT @IGN: .@SpidermanMovie @1VictoriaAngela: Did you go through any diet or intensive workout for the role? #AskDaneDeHaan
(cont.) but still play superheroes all day long! @IGN @spideypromise -DD
.@IGN @spideypromise It's my childhood dreams meeting my adult dreams...I get to work with great people on a challenging role...
RT @IGN: .@SpiderManMovie @spideypromise: What was the best thing about joining TASM cast and fan base? #AskDaneDeHaan
